{"key":"post-11520807","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11520807</id>\n<content>The soak helps to germinate some of the bacterial endospores, making them easier to kill in the pressure cooker.&amp;nbsp; In my opinion, it's equally important for hydrating the grains slowly.&amp;nbsp; If you put dry grains into water and boil or PC, you'll end up with a lot of burst kernels.&amp;nbsp; In the old days, we added dry grains, a pinch of gypsum, and water to jars and then PCd it like that.&amp;nbsp; It was much faster, but we also had a lot of burst kernels and higher rates of bacterial contamination then we do now following more modern procedures.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>11520619</prev>\n<first>11520092</first>\n<last>11520807</last>\n<when>1259110474</when>\n<utime>11/25/09 02:54 AM</utime>\n</post>"}